                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: ʿAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ. ʿAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication formula on <locus target="#4rb">4rb</locus>.<date>First half of the 20th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም </expan> (<locus target="#67vb">67vb</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; names of the
                           scribe and the donors; groups of lines (alternating with black lines) in
                           the incipit page; a few lines on fol. 46va; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#68v">Fol. 68v: </locus>
                        <desc>St. Kiros</desc>Legend: ʾAbuna Kiros “Our Father Kiros”</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#70r">f. 70r</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#70r">70r</locus>: ናይ ቐቐማ ገዳም ደብረ ገነት</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is crudely written in pen in Tǝgrǝñña. It states that the
                              book belongs to the Dabra Gannat Qäqäma monastery. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters and words are written interlineally, in
                           the main hand: <locus target="#4vb">4vb</locus>, 5rb, 8ra, 11rb, 11vb,
                           12v, 19vb, 20r, 20vb, 22rb, 25rb, 26ra, 27va, 31va, 35rb, 37rb,
                           52vb.
 - Omitted letters and words are written interlineally, in a
                           secondary hand, in pen: 7vab, 8ra, 11ra
 - Some letters or words are
                           underlined with a pink pen throughout the Ms.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days written in the upper margin, in a secondary hand, in pen: ዘሰኑይ:
                                 <locus target="#3ra">fol. 3ra</locus> ሰሉስ: <locus target="#14rb">fol. 14rb</locus> ረውዕ[sic]: <locus target="#21vb">fol.
                                 21vb</locus> ሐሙሽ[sic]: <locus target="#30ra">fol. 30ra</locus> ዓርብ:
                                 <locus target="#40rb">fol. 40rb</locus> ቐዳም[sic]: <locus target="#49va">fol. 49va</locus> ሰንበት: <locus target="#56vb">fol.
                                 56vb</locus>. The beginning of the reading is marked in the text
                              with a sign of cross.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with reddish-brown tooled
                           leather; textile inlays.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes are visible in the centre
                           fold of the quires, one close to the head and one close to the tail of
                           the codex.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the reddish-brown leather
                           cover (at least 4 tools were used: triple line fillet, double circle,
                           braid, cross hatching).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
